      <body>
         <pb n="1" facs="../images/ew_b_001.jpg"/>
         <figure>
            <desc><!-- Taken from University of North Florida Special Collections, Eartha M.M. White Collection, Folder B, no item number.-->
            <address>
               <addrLine>           
                  The Afro-American Life Insurance Company<lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine rendition="#capitalize">
                  Incorporated under the laws of Florida<lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  Paid up capital stock$150,000.00<lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="person">A.L. Lewis</name>, president
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="person">J.H. Lewis</name>, vice president<lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="person">Louis D. Ervin</name>, cashier
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="person">William H. Lee</name>, secretary<lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="place">Home Office</name> <name type="place" subtype="address"> 101-105 E. Union Street<location><geo>30.331966 -81.654918</geo></location></name><lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="place">Office of President</name> <lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="place" subtype="address">P.O. Box 660</name><lb/>
               </addrLine>
               <addrLine>
                  <name type="place" subtype="city">Jacksonville, Florida</name><lb/>
               </addrLine>
            </address>
         </desc><graphic url="../images/ew_b_001_001.jpg"></graphic>
         </figure>
         
         <opener>
                  <date when="1936-01-18">January <space/>18<choice><orig>-</orig><reg>,</reg></choice> 1936</date><lb/>
                  <address>
                     <addrLine>
                        <name type="person">Miss Eartha White</name><lb/>
                     </addrLine>
                     <addrLine>
                        <name type="place" subtype="building">611 West Ashley Street</name><location><geo>30.332490 -81.664152</geo></location><lb/>
                     </addrLine>
                     <addrLine>
                        Jacksonville, Florida<lb/>
                     </addrLine>
                  </address>
                  <salute>
                     My dear <name type="person">Miss White</name>:<lb/>
                  </salute>
         </opener>


         <p>
            
            I noticed recently your publication with reference<lb/>
            to <supplied reason="omitted-in-original" cert="high">the</supplied><name type="organization"> History Society for Jacksonville Negroes</name>.<lb/>
            I have always felt that <choice><orig>some one</orig><reg>someone</reg></choice> should write a<lb/>
            history of the <name type="person_group">Negroes</name> of our <name type="place">city</name>, as far back<lb/>
            as we can get information, so that in future years<lb/>
            the young generation will know of some of the<lb/>
            accomplishments and hardships. You have my hearty<lb/>
            support and if I can be of any service to you, <lb/>
            call on me.<lb/> 
      </p>
      <p>
         <name type="person">Mayor Aslop</name> called me and stated that he wanted to <lb/>
         appoint you and myself as an <name type="committee">Advisory Committee</name> on<lb/>
         the <name type="legislation">Slum Housing Act</name>, and ask that I talk with <lb/>
         <name type="person">Mr. Bradshaw</name>, who I saw this morning and he<lb/>
         suggested that we talk with <name type="person">Mr. Edwards</name> in <name type="place">Barnett<lb/>
         Bank building<location><geo>30.328120 -81.659319</geo></location></name> next Monday or Tuesday. Please get<lb/>
         in touch with me for this meeting. 
      </p>
      <p>
          May I wish for you continued good health and success. 
      </p>

         <closer style="mid-page">
               <salute>
                      Very truly yours,<lb/>
               </salute>
               <signed>
                  <name type="person"> <name type="person">A.L. Lewis</name>,<name role="administrator">  PRESIDENT</name></name>.<lb/>
               </signed>
            
            </closer>
      <closer style="left">
         ALL- eaj 
      </closer>
    
